fferent requests for specific data points or some investor&#8217;s favorite=
 metric based on their experience with another quasi-analogous company. It =
was also as certain as death and taxes that an investor would see a number,=
 take it out of context, and blow up its importance, wasting hours of the e=
xec team and data team&#8217;s time.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">As an investor &#821=
1; albeit a non-lead one usually without data rights &#8211; I&#8217;m at t=
he mercy of whatever founders decide to put in that month or quarter&#8217;=
